main event: On 23 September 1951, an unidentified object was reported near Long Beach, California, leading to the scramble of F-86 aircraft to investigate.
interesting points: The object was initially described as being round and silver, with an altitude estimated between 50,000 to 55,000 feet., The object was eventually evaluated as possibly being a radiosonde balloon., Four F-86 pilots attempted to visually intercept the object but were unable to do so., At one point, the object was reported to be in a left orbit at approximately 4,000 feet., Weather balloons had been launched from nearby stations shortly before the sighting.
sighted object: unidentified object believed to be a balloon
witness description: F-86 pilots and military personnel involved in the interception.
